		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1"> I've been playing a warrior on rallos for 2 years straight, and to answer your question, I'd say no. Verant is brilliant at designing pve (hence why the game is so famous and addictive) but in terms of pvp, they've always been clueless. It wasn't so bad a few months ago, but the new resist system is the last nail in eq pvp's coffin. With this new system, you can be rooted at 200+ mr quite frequently, giving us melees a SERIOUS disadvantage in pvp. Also, they made resist debuffs 50% more potent than usual a while back, screwing us over even more. You rogues are controversial in pvp regards - a skilled rogue spells death to a melee, yet no matter how good you are, casters will always trash rogues. On the subject of economy on Rallos, it's quite different than on the other servers. I'll sum it to you this way - items with resists basically are double-price than other servers, and things without resists are about half of their standard prices. On the other hand, though, I'd LOVE for more people like you to come here. Rallos is, and always has been, a very underpopulated server and we need more people!<BR>            <BR>           -Zan<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
