 friend of mine just shortly before this incident, and the shaman's regen would completely cancel out the effect of the druid's dots, making this druid bitch about me being buffed to the zone repeatedly. So then the druid found a way to exploit. He somehow climbed to the top of an ice pillar in everfrost (he didn't have levitate, so I don't know how) which I couldn't climb on, even with sow. As I am a warrior, I was kinda screwed in this battle - he could simply sit on the top of the pillar and repeatedly nuke me until I died. I went linkdead while this was happening and came back only to see that my hp hadn't dropped at all and that he had logged. As I stupidly can't remember his name, I wasn't able to petition him - but the point is that the game mechanics on pvp servers shouldn't allow things like that to be possible.</P><P> These extremely common acts on RZ are what have compelled me to combat the seemingly endless swarm of "12 year olds", also known as being an anti-pk. I have no problem with skilled solo pks, as that's what RZ was made for, but group-killing helpless people who are fighting mobs isn't right. It also isn't illegal.</P><P>     -Zan<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
