		<hr size="1">Rallos, eh? Never had the pleasure... ony PvP server I've had experience with is Sullen... might be fun... I'm sure that it will stink when I do ( and I guarantee I will) get owned, but isn't that the point. If you get owned, then you get owned.</P><P>Somethings that do stink, though.</P><P>Corpse camping... kinda lame. at least let the puke you killed loot and scoot. Now, if they don't leave zone.. waste 'em! That was my rule.</P><P>Don't bitch if what you expected wasn't what you got. Sorry you didn't realize I had an air pet up that was invisible. Chit happens, deal.</P><P>When killed, you loot and scoot. They owned you, their zone, not yours. If you don;t leave, expect to get owned again.</P><P>Got killed after a Rez? Your fault for trusting someone without knowing them first.</P><P>Got killed after zoning? Wahhhh... happens, and quite often.</P><P><BR>One thing I always did is compliment the person who just owned me. SOunds like ass-kissing. It is, in a way. Essentially, what I am telling the person is,"You owned me, and that's all good. I'm coming to loot my body, and get out of Dodge."</P><P>The other thing that I would do is tell the person I just owned about a weak point I took advantage of. "Hey, if hunting MOBS leaves you that low on life you should get a partner." and that sort of thing. I figure what fun is PvP if you don't help each other improve. Makes for stiffer competition.</P><P><BR>This is just one man's perspective. These are the rules I have lived by on PvP. I'm not here to ruin someone's entire day. Maybe 10 minutes of it. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
